  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "intro-0",
      "sectionId": "intro",
      "title": "Intro",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "A cheatsheet for GnuPG, the encryption and signing software."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-1",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Software",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Gpg4win and the GPG Suite have OS-specific features."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-2",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Software",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "• [GnuPG](https://gnupg.org/)\n• [Gpg4win](https://www.gpg4win.org/) (Windows)\n• [GPG Suite](https://gpgtools.org/) (macOS)"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-3",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Software",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Sometimes GPG keys are referred as PGP keys. They're interchangeable, as they follow the\n[OpenPGP Standard](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9580.html)."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-4",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Generate your keys:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-5",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "```shell script\n$ gpg --generate-key"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-6",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n... or fully configure your keys."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-7",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --generate-full-keys"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-8",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n**Note:** Choose a strong passphrase! The encryption is only as strong as your passphrase.\n\n### Key management\n\nList your keys:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-9",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --list-keys"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-10",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nList your secret keys:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-11",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --list-secret-keys"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-12",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nExport your public key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-13",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --export --armor <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-14",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nExport your secret key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-15",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --export-secret-key --armor <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-16",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nDelete your public key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-17",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --delete-key <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-18",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nDelete your secret key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-19",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --delete-secret-key <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-20",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n## Encryption\n\n### Symmetric\n\nEncrypt with a passphrase:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-21",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -c <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-22",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nEncrypt as ASCII with `-a` flag:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-23",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -ac <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-24",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSet output file path with `-o` flag:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-25",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -c <FILE> -o <PATH>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-26",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nDecrypt with a passphrase:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-27",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-28",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n**Note:** Choose a strong passphrase! The encryption is only as strong as your passphrase.\n\n### Asymmetric\n\nEncrypt using public-private key encryption:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-29",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -e -r <RECIPIENT> <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-30",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nEncrypt as ASCII output with `-a` flag:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-31",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -ea -r <RECIPIENT> <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-32",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nEncrypt and sign with `-s` flag:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-33",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -se -r <RECIPIENT> <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-34",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nAdd multiple recipients:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-35",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -e -r <RECIPIENT1> -r <RECIPIENT2> <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-36",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSet output file path with `-o` flag:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-37",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg -e -o <PATH> -r <RECIPIENT> <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-38",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nDecrypt with your private key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-39",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-40",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nReplace `<RECIPIENT>` with your intended recipient's [imported public key](#importing-a-public-key) ID.\n\n### Importing a public key\n\nImport using a file:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-41",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --import <FILE>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-42",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nImport using a link (macOS/Linux):"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-43",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ curl <WEBSITE> | gpg --import"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-44",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nDon't forget to sign the imported key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-45",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --sign-key <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-46",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n## Commit Signing\n\n### Local Git Setup\n\nEnable GPG signing:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-47",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ git config --global commit.gpgsign true"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-48",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSet the signing key:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-49",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ git config --global user.signingkey <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-50",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSet location of GPG:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-51",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ git config --global gpg.program <PROGRAM>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-52",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n**Note:** Your name and email must match on Git and GnuPG.\n\n### GPG Program List\n\nReplace `<PROGRAM>` with one of the following:\n\n| Platform    | Value                                      |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n| Windows     | `C:\\Program Files (x86)\\GnuPG\\bin\\gpg.exe` |\n| macOS/Linux | /usr/local/bin/gpg                         |\n\n{.left-text}\n\n### Exporting your public key\n\nExport as ASCII:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-53",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpg --export --armor <ID>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-54",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n**Note:** Platforms, like GitHub, may ask you to verify the email you set in Git and GnuPG.\n\n## Windows: Add to Startup Apps {.cols-1}\n\n### PowerShell Commands\n\nWhen you do a full restart, the GPG agent might not automatically start. Add the GnuPG's IPC tool to Startup Apps using\nPowerShell:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-55",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ $shell = New-Object -ComObject WScript.Shell\n$ $shortcut = $shell.CreateShortcut(\"C:\\Users\\$($Env:UserName)\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup\\gpg-connect-agent.lnk\")\n$ $shortcut.TargetPath = \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\GnuPG\\bin\\gpg-connect-agent.exe\"\n$ $shortcut.Arguments = \"/bye\"\n$ $shortcut.Save()"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-56",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nStart up manually instead:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-57",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ gpgconf --launch gpg-agent"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-58",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCheck if it was successfully added [here](ms-settings:startupapps)."
    }
  ],
